1) Try to open history manager from system settings.
2) Try to open history manager from Kmenu.
3) Try to Take snapshot	
    - Install or remove a package from package manager.
    - Push take snapshot button from history manager.
    - Observe that after taking snapshot whether the history manager screen can be refreshed and show new changes.

4) Try to push details button for a date.
    Go console and type 
    pisi hs
    Compare the last changes with history manager according to related date. 

5) Try to push Show operation plan button for a date.
     Go console and type·
     $ pisi hs
     - Compare the last changes with history manager for the related date.
        Observe that the package(s) will be updated, installed or removed correctly.

6) Try to push Take Changes Back button for a date.
    - After taking changes back 
        6.a) Observe whether the history manager screen can be refreshed.
        6.b) Push the show operations button of the related time that you had taken the operation(s) back.
            - Observe that operation(s) had been removed from the show operation plan list.
     	6.c) Go console and type·
     	    $ pisi hs
     	    - Compare the last changes with history manager.
            Observe that the operations that had taken back are listed correctly.

